# Keep docker builds reproducible from source — never let host build
# artifacts sneak into the image via `COPY . .`. The Dockerfile's
# multi-stage chain is the only authoritative builder; if a package's
# dist/ ends up in the image, it must come from that chain, not from
# whatever the developer happened to run locally.
#
# Production lesson (2026-05-08): missing `pnpm --filter
# @hearth/verification-core build` in the Dockerfile chain went
# undetected for days because every developer's host `dist/` masked
# the bug. Fresh `git clone` on the VM finally exposed it.

# Build outputs — every workspace package emits these.
**/dist/
**/.next/
**/.turbo/
**/coverage/
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# Workspace install artefacts — pnpm reinstalls fresh inside the image.
**/node_modules/

# Local-only dotfiles + secrets.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
**/.env
**/.env.*
**/!.env.example

# Editor / OS noise.
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp

# Git metadata isn't needed for the build (Sentry release tracking
# would consume it, but we don't run that in the Dockerfile).
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# CI-only files.
.github/

# Test fixtures and transient runner state.
**/*.test.ts.snap
.lefthook-cache/

# Documentation — not needed inside the runtime image. Drop only the
# big trees; runbook docs are tiny but irrelevant to the bundle.
docs/
*.md
!apps/bot/README.md
!apps/dashboard/README.md
